L2_gloss: Part of maize that is given to someone as a thank you for the maize they helped to pick.
grain, seed or small fruit of some plants
morning, time that elapses from sunrise to noon
medium house, house smaller than the main one.
guide, person who knows the roads, accesses and shortcuts
candle, cylindrical piece made of wax with a wick in
window, small hole in a wall for lighting or ventilation
a potato that is dark inside
party, a meeting in which liquor is drunk
lap, upper legs; Part of the body between the waist and the knee.
blanket, cape; Long garment that covers most of the body.
Any piece or part of a clay pot.
crust, crumb; Piece or fragment of something.
